  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This activity (British Support for Infrastructure Projects uses blending grants to increase affordability of government loans for infrastructure, support delivery of high-quality public infra projects at sustainable rates &amp; partner countries&#x2019; green transitions) is a component of British Support for Infrastructure Projects (BSIP) (formerly Developing Markets Infrastructure Programme (DMIP) reported by FCDO, with a funding type of &apos;Procurement of Services&apos; and a budget of &#xA3;390,000,000. This component benefits Developing countries, unspecified, and works in the following sector(s): Water supply and sanitation - large systems, Public sector policy and administrative management, Transport policy and administrative management, Telecommunications, Energy generation, renewable sources - multiple technologies. The start date is 01-02-2022 and the end date is 31-03-2036.</narrative>
  </description>
